<subSubSection id="D5A5E7CA6A11FFEEFEA8FAB08B5CF94E" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9D00B4416A11FFEEFEA8FAB08AEBFA06" blockId="6.[264,1325,284,1870]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="AFCB68536A11FFEEFEA8FAB089C0FA8D" box="[312,440,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Discussion</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="F92EC9B06A11FFEEFE5AFAB08B05FA8E" author="Schwoerbel" box="[458,893,1364,1390]" pageId="6" pageNumber="8" refString="Schwoerbel, J. &amp; Sepasgosarian, H. (1980) Wassermilben (Acari, Prostigmata, Hydrachnellae) aus dem Iran. 8. Mitteilung. Subterrane Sußwassermilben. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg, 6 (107), 293 - 301." type="journal article" year="1980">
Schwoerbel &amp; Sepasgosarian (
<number id="2B77A6666A11FFEEFCA8FAB08B0DFA8E" box="[824,885,1364,1390]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1980.0">1980</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported the presence of 
<taxonomicName id="5ABFCFC26A11FFEEFB22FAB08904FA75" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Axonopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inferorum">
<emphasis id="AFCB68536A11FFEEFB22FAB08904FA75" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Axonopsis inferorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="F92EC9B06A11FFEEFE15FA988ACFFA76" author="MotaS" box="[389,695,1404,1430]" pageId="6" pageNumber="8" refString="Motas, C., Tanasachi, J. &amp; Orghidan, T. (1947) Hydracariens phreaticoles de Roumanie. Notationes Biologicae, 5 (1 - 3), 1 - 67." type="journal article" year="1947">
MotaŞ &amp; Tanasachi, 
<quantity id="5A4719A46A11FFEEFDECFA988ACFFA76" box="[636,695,1404,1430]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.94538" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="in" value="1947.0">1947</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
in 
<collectingCountry id="E5A8F4D16A11FFEEFD4EFA988B69FA76" box="[734,785,1404,1430]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Iran</collectingCountry>
. However, from an examination of the specimen conservated under this name in the collection Schwoerbel resulted fundamental differences (
<bibRefCitation id="F92EC9B06A11FFEEFEE9FA288AFFFA06" author="Pesic" box="[377,647,1484,1510]" pageId="6" pageNumber="8" refString="Pesic, V. &amp; Gerecke, R. (2003). Water mites of the genera Albaxona, Axonopsis, Barbaxonella and Erebaxonopsis (Acari, Hydrachnidia: Aturidae: Axonopsinae) from Central Europe and Mediterranean area. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Suppl. 139 (4), 563 - 576." type="journal article" year="2003">
Pesic &amp; Gerecke 
<number id="2B77A6666A11FFEEFDD7FA288AFFFA06" box="[583,647,1484,1510]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D00B4416A11FFEEFEA8FA108B5CF94E" blockId="6.[264,1325,284,1870]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="5ABFCFC26A11FFEEFEA8FA108A62F9ED" box="[312,538,1524,1549]" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Axonopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gereckei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="AFCB68536A11FFEEFEA8FA108A62F9ED" box="[312,538,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Axonopsis gereckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B4F8D5286A11FFEEFDB1FA108A04F9EE" box="[545,636,1524,1550]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from all known species of the subgenus 
<emphasis id="AFCB68536A11FFEEFEA8F9F88984F9D5" box="[312,508,1564,1589]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="5ABFCFC26A11FFEEFEA8F9F88980F9D5" box="[312,504,1564,1589]" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Brachypodopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Brachypodopsis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
in the combination of well developed postocularia and a slight development of a cauda in the male. Furthermore, it differs from 
<taxonomicName id="5ABFCFC26A11FFEEFC51F9A08C2DF9BD" box="[961,1109,1604,1629]" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Axonopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inferorum">
<emphasis id="AFCB68536A11FFEEFC51F9A08C2DF9BD" box="[961,1109,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. inferorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the presence of two distinct pairs of glandularia between the insertions of the fourth legs and the genital field (one pair of glandularia in 
<taxonomicName id="5ABFCFC26A11FFEEFDEEF9708B6BF94D" box="[638,787,1684,1709]" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Axonopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inferorum">
<emphasis id="AFCB68536A11FFEEFDEEF9708B6BF94D" box="[638,787,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. inferorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D5A5E7CA6A11FFEEFEA8F9588CE5F936" box="[312,1181,1724,1750]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="9D00B4416A11FFEEFEA8F9588CE5F936" blockId="6.[264,1325,284,1870]" box="[312,1181,1724,1750]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="AFCB68536A11FFEEFEA8F95889C6F935" box="[312,446,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology:</emphasis>
The species is named after Dr. Reinhard Gerecke (Tübingen).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D5A5E7CA6A11FFEEFEA8F9008BD4F91E" box="[312,940,1764,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9D00B4416A11FFEEFEA8F9008BD4F91E" blockId="6.[264,1325,284,1870]" box="[312,940,1764,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="AFCB68536A11FFEEFEA8F90089A9F91D" box="[312,465,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="E5A8F4D16A11FFEEFE41F9008A7CF91E" box="[465,516,1764,1790]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Iran</collectingCountry>
; only known from the 
<emphasis id="AFCB68536A11FFEEFC9DF9008BDDF91D" box="[781,933,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">locus typicus</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D5A5E7CA6A11FFEFFEA8F8E889CDFEBE" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="9D00B4416A11FFEFFEA8F8E889CDFEBE" blockId="6.[264,1325,284,1870]" lastBlockId="7.[264,1323,284,350]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="AFCB68536A11FFEEFEA8F8E88AFFF8C5" box="[312,647,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Biology: 
<taxonomicName id="5ABFCFC26A11FFEEFE34F8E88AFFF8C5" box="[420,647,1804,1829]" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Axonopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gereckei" status="sp. nov.">Axonopsis gereckei</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B4F8D5286A11FFEEFD1FF8E88A93F8C6" box="[655,747,1804,1830]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is probably a hyporheobiont. Larvae of 
<taxonomicName id="5ABFCFC26A11FFEEFB57F8E8895FF8AD" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Axonopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AFCB68536A11FFEEFB57F8E8895FF8AD" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Axonopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species were found parasitic on Chironomid midges in 
<collectingCountry id="E5A8F4D16A11FFEEFC3EF8D08C6BF8AE" box="[942,1043,1844,1870]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">America</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F92EC9B06A11FFEEFBB2F8D08D66F8AE" author="Smith" box="[1058,1310,1844,1870]" pageId="6" pageNumber="8" refString="Smith, I. M. &amp; Oliver, D. R. (1986) Review of parasitic associations of larval water mites (Acari: Parasitengona: Hydrachnida) with insect hosts. Canadian Entomologist, 118, 407 - 472." type="journal article" year="1986">
Smith &amp; Oliver 
<number id="2B77A6666A11FFEEFB4FF8D08D66F8AE" box="[1247,1310,1844,1870]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but no data are available on the behaviour of larvae of palaearctic species (
<bibRefCitation id="F92EC9B06A10FFEFFB57FEF889D6FEBE" author="Pesic" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Pesic, V. &amp; Gerecke, R. (2003). Water mites of the genera Albaxona, Axonopsis, Barbaxonella and Erebaxonopsis (Acari, Hydrachnidia: Aturidae: Axonopsinae) from Central Europe and Mediterranean area. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Suppl. 139 (4), 563 - 576." type="journal article" year="2003">
Pesic &amp; Gerecke 
<number id="2B77A6666A10FFEFFEE1FEA089D6FEBE" box="[369,430,324,350]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
